# Data Layer

- All persistence lives behind repositories in `repositories.dart`; each takes an `AppDatabase`.
- Tables are defined in `db/tables.dart`. After changing them, bump `schemaVersion` in `app_database.dart`, add an `onUpgrade` step, and run `dart run build_runner build`.

## Avoid N+1 queries

Bulk-load and join in memory instead of querying inside a loop.

```dart
// BAD: one query per account
for (final a in accounts) { await latestSnapshot(a.id); }

// GOOD: one query, group in Dart
final snaps = await (select(balanceSnapshots)
      ..orderBy([(t) => OrderingTerm.desc(t.recordedAt)])).get();
final byAccount = <int, BalanceSnapshot>{};
for (final s in snaps) { byAccount.putIfAbsent(s.accountId, () => s); }
```

## FX snapshots

Never hand-roll FX snapshot inserts. Use the single source of truth `AppDatabase.insertFxSnapshot(...)` (or `FxRepository.insertSnapshot`), which writes the snapshot plus one `USD -> X` rate row per supported currency and falls back to `defaultUsdRate(currency)` for any currency omitted from the `usdRates` map.

## Reactivity

Expose `Stream`s for data the UI observes. `AppDatabase.dashboardChanges()` emits on every net-worth-relevant table change; wrap aggregate computations in `async*` that re-yield on it (see `SessionRepository.watchFamilyTrend`).
